
10-01-2024
Program solving with javaScript:
1)Write program to check whether the number is divisible by 2 and 3 and both (take prompt)
2)Write a program to find the largest number out of three numbers expected from the user
A=11
B=5
C=8
3)Accept the following from the user and calculate the percentage of classes attended:
a)Total number of working days
b)Total number of days for absent
After calculating percentages show that,if the percentage is less than 75, then student will not be eligible to write exam
4)A company decided to give bonus to employee according to the following criteria:
Time period of service                Bonus
More than 10 Years                     10%
>=6  and <=10                                8%
Less than 6 years                          5%
Ask the user for their salary and years of service and print the bonus amount
1)problem code:
     let number = parseInt(prompt("Enter a number:"));
       if (number % 2 === 0 && number % 3 === 0) {
            document.write("The number is divisible by both 2 and 3.");
        } else if (number % 2 === 0) {
            document.write("The number is divisible by 2.");
        } else if (number % 3 === 0) {
            document.write("The number is divisible by 3.");
        } else {
    document.write("The number is not divisible by 2 or 3.");
}
2)problem code:
let a = parseInt(prompt("Enter the first number:"));
        let b = parseInt(prompt("Enter the second number:"));
        let c = parseInt(prompt("Enter the third number:"));
        if(a>b && a>c){
            document.write(`${a} is greater b and c1`)
        }else if (b>a && b>c){
            document.write(`${b} is greater a and c`)
        }else{
            document.write(`{c} is greater than a and b`)
        }
     3)problem code:
<script>
        let W = parseInt(prompt("Enter total number of days"))
        let A = parseInt(prompt("Enter number of Absent days"))
        let P = W -A
        let AP=(P/W)*100
        if(AP>=75){
            document.write("Eligible")
        }else{
            document.write("Not Eligible")
        }  
    </script>
4)problem code:
  let a=parseInt(prompt("salary"))
        let b=parseInt(prompt("years of service"))
        if(b>10){
            let c=a*0.1
            let d=c+a
            alert("after bonus salary"+d)
        }
        else if(b>=6 && b<=10){
            let c=a*0.08
            let d=c+a
            alert("after bonus salary"+d)
        }
        else if(b<6){
            let c=a*0.05
            let d=c+a
            alert("after bonus salary"+a)
        }
        else{
            alert(a)
        }

